     CODESPECT

     7.7     [Medium] notesCount is not updated during the execution of updateNotes(...)
     File(s): NoteAccount.cairo
     Description: The notesCount storage mapping tracks the number of notes associated with each public key.
     However, this value is not updated during the execution of updateNotes(...). As a result, after a note update, the stored count may no
     longer reflect the actual number of notes. The internal eraseNotes(...) function should reset the note count to zero, and during the loop
     in updateNotes(...), the count should be incremented on each iteration.

1    loop {
2        self.notes.entry(pubKey).entry(i.into()).write((
3            *newNotes[i][0], *newNotes[i][1], *newNotes[i][2],
4            *newNotes[i][3], *newNotes[i][4], *newNotes[i][5],
5            *newNotes[i][6]
6        ));
7        i += 1;
8        if (newNotes.len() == i) {
9            break;
10       }
11       // @audit update the note count
12   }

     Impact: Incorrect tracking of note counts can lead to inconsistencies and unexpected behavior in contract logic that depends on the
     accurate number of notes per public key.
     Recommendation(s): Ensure eraseNotes(...) resets the count to zero, and increment notesCount in each iteration of the update loop
     to maintain consistency.
     Status: Fixed
     Update from Typhoon: Solved 1fa6a6d6462c66d8ce271b077a0420a7bcbfafdf
